Bought this for my father in law who needs to be gluten free. I have tried some of his gluten free beers over the years and let's just say thank goodness I can tolerate gluten. This was the first gluten free beer that I could ever see myself drinking. Pours dark brown with a huge foam head. Nose of some coffee and a strange phony floral smell (which was all that was apparent in the other gluten free beers I have tried). Taste has some coffee and oatmeal - there is a bit of a funky taste, too, which I guess is the sorghum. This is not a great beer, but it is fine and may be as good as gluten free gets.
